To deploy a workload on Google Cloud Pub/Sub, you can follow these steps as described in the provided context:

1. First, use Terraform to deploy a Pub/Sub function [Source: gcp/Cloud Functions/Terraform Pub/Sub Tutorial]. The main.tf file is provided below:

```hcl
terraform {
  required_providers {
    google = {
      source  = "hashicorp/google"
      version = ">= 4.34.0"
    }
  }
}

resource "random_id" "bucket_prefix" {
  byte_length = 8
}

resource "google_service_account" "default" {
  account_id   = "test-gcf-sa"
  display_name = "Test Service Account"
}
```

2. Locally test your function using the provided Go code [Source: gcp/Cloud Functions/Locally test your function > Cloud Pub/Sub event-driven function example > Go]. Here is the relevant code:

```go
package helloworld

import (
  "context"
  "fmt"
  "log"
  "github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/functions-framework-go/functions"
  "github.com/cloudevents/sdk-go/v2/event"
)

func init() {
  functions.CloudEvent("HelloPubSub", helloPubSub)
}

// helloPubSub consumes a CloudEvent message and extracts the Pub/Sub message.
func helloPubSub(ctx context.Context, e event.Event) error {
  // ... (code for handling the Pub/Sub message omitted)
}
```

3. Prepare the application by following the steps in [Source: gcp/Cloud Functions/Terraform Pub/Sub Tutorial > Preparing the application]. This includes cloning the sample app repository and changing to the directory that contains the Cloud Run functions sample code.
